WinWota 2.0 Product Contract (always apply unless a prompt explicitly overrides)

UI/UX
- Target users are expert Olympic weightlifting coaches and athletes; prioritize information density and low interaction cost over “spacious” layouts.
- Prefer compact tables, tight spacing, and scan-friendly hierarchy (bold titles, small secondary text).
- Avoid wizard flows and excessive modals. Prefer inline editing where appropriate.
- Any “planned” data is coach-authored and must remain read-only for athlete-facing views; athlete edits must go into log entities only.

Formatting
- Use dd/mm/yyyy for all date display and input (Europe/Denmark). Do not show mm/dd/yyyy anywhere.
- Prescription notation rules:
  - Input supports "load x reps" (implies sets=1) and "load x reps x sets" (explicit sets), comma-separated segments.
  - When sets=1, never display the “×1” sets part.
- Read-only display can use Stacked Load Notation (load on top, reps below a divider, sets on the right) for kg/%/RPE when enabled per exercise.

Architecture / Slices
- Build in small vertical slices. Do not introduce unrelated features, packages, or refactors.
- Reuse existing data models and naming; do not rename types/fields unless prompted.
- Add non-goals explicitly and do not implement them.

Styling
- Clean, professional, compact. Avoid “marketing site” aesthetics.
- Use Tailwind + Lucide only (no extra UI libraries unless requested).